04777nam a22009135i 9781487513900DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20202021onc    fo  d z      eng d  a97814875139007 a10.3138/97814875139002doi  a(DE-B1597)570780  a(OCoLC)1226362630  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aonccCA-ON 4aHD1286b.O24 2021 7aBUS0690002bisacsh1 aObeng-Odoom, Franklin , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Commons in an Age of Uncertainty :bDecolonizing Nature, Economy, and Society /cFranklin Obeng-Odoom. 1aToronto : bUniversity of Toronto Press, c[2020] 4cÂ©2021  a1 online resource (280 p.) :b7 figures  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tPart A: The Problem -- t1 The Age of Uncertainty -- tPart B: The Debates and a Path through Them -- t2 Historical Debates on the Commons -- t3 Rethinking the Commons -- tPart C: The Proof -- t4 Cities -- t5 Technology -- t6 Oil -- t7 Water -- tPart D: The Future of the Commons -- t8 Concluding Remarks: Towards a New Ecological Political Economy -- tReferences -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn the last two hundred years, the earth has increasingly become the private property of a few classes, races, transnational corporations, and nations. Repeated claims about the "tragedy of the commons" and the "crisis of capitalism" have done little to explain this concentration of land, encourage solution-building to solve resource depletion, or address our current socio-ecological crisis. The Commons in an Age of Uncertainty presents a new explanation, vision, and action plan based on the idea of commoning the land. The book argues that by commoning the land, rather than privatising it, we can develop the foundation for prosperity without destructive growth and address both local and global challenges. Making the land the most fundamental priority of all commons does not only give hope, it also opens the doors to a new world in which economy, environment, and society are decolonised and liberated.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aCommons. 0aDecolonization. 0aPublic lands. 0aRight of property. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh  acities.  aclimate change.  acommons.  aeconomy.  aenvironment.  ahardin.  aland.  anature.  aostrom.  asustainability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751390040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487513900423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487513900/original  a978-3-11-069045-3  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070479-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBVb2020  aZDB-23-DGGb2020